    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-04-19T13:58:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-04-19T13:58:00-05:00" n="25"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <head>25. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to
                    Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_RD1" type="to">Rusk</persName> at
                        Saigon<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d25fn1">Source: Department of State,
                        Central Files, POL 27 VIET S. Secret; Flash; <gloss target="#t_Exdis1"
                            >Exdis</gloss>. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_GM1">Green</persName>,
                        cleared in substance by <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName> and
                            <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">McGeorge Bundy</persName>, cleared in draft
                        by <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">U. Alexis Johnson</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_TLE1">Thompson</persName>, and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_BGW1">Ball</persName>. Repeated immediate to
                        Vientiane.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-04-19T13:58:00-05:00">April 19, 1964, 1:58 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 70. For Secretary from Acting Secretary
                    and Secretary <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName>. We would
                    appreciate your views soonest on desirability unadvertised movement of US
                    forces, such as naval units toward North Viet-Nam, in order to deter and
                    discourage North Viet-Nam or other communist elements from military exploitation
                    of current confused situation in Laos. Such movements would obviously have to be
                    carried out in such manner that coup government in Vientiane does not feel it
                    has blank check from <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> and also so that there
                    is a credible innocuous explanation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Ball</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
